==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[ice cream|ice cream]]'' + ''[[cone]]'' (a hollow cone)

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg|ice cream cone}}

# A thin, conical confection baked from [[crepe]] [[batter]], sealed at its apex, used to hold ice cream while it is being eaten.  Synonym: [[cornet]]
# Any sweet, edible cone or half-open cylinder which can be used in this fashion
# An ice cream cone filled with [[ice cream]]. <!-- Synonym: [[ice cream]] -->